{"kanda":6,"sarga":121,"description":"","verses":[{"v":1,"dev":"एतच्छ्रुत्वाशुभंवाक्यंपितामहसमीरितम् ।अङ्केनादायवैदेहिमुत्पपातविभावसुः","trans":"On hearing creator Brahma's address to Rama, fire god emerged picking auspicious Vaidehi in his arms.","words":[{"d":"विभावसुः","m":"fire god"},{"d":"पितामहसमीरितम्","m":"address of Brahma"},{"d":"शुभम्","m":"auspicious"},{"d":"एतत्","m":"these"},{"d":"वाक्यम्","m":"words"},{"d":"श्रुत्वा","m":"hearing"},{"d":"वैदेहीम्","m":"Vaidehi"},{"d":"अङ्केन","m":"under arms"},{"d":"आदाय","m":"picking"},{"d":"उत्पपात","m":"arose"}]},{"v":2,"dev":"नविधूयाथचितांतांतुवैदेहींहव्यवाहनः ।उत्तस्थौमूर्तिमानाशुगृहीत्वाजनकात्मजाम्","trans":"Then the fire god taking human form emerged from the fire immediately,with Janaka's daughter shaking off the fire sticks.","words":[{"d":"अथ","m":"and then"},{"d":"हव्यवाहनः","m":"fire god"},{"d":"मूर्तिमान्","m":"taking human form"},{"d":"आशु","m":"immediately"},{"d":"ताम्","m":"those"},{"d":"चिताम्","m":"firesticks"},{"d":"विधूय","m":"shaking off"},{"d":"जनकात्मजाम्","m":"janaka's daughter"},{"d":"तांवैदेहीम्","m":"that Vaidehi"},{"d":"गृहीत्वा","m":"taking"},{"d":"उत्तस्थौ","m":"emerged"}]},{"v":3,"dev":"तरुणादित्यसङ्काशंतप्तकाञ्चनभूषणाम् ।रक्ताम्बरधरांबालांसीलकुञ्चितमूर्थजाम् अक्लिष्टमाल्याभरणांतथारूपामनिन्दिताम् ।ददौरामायवैदेहीमङ्केकृत्वाविभावसुः","trans":"Radiating like the rising sun, adorned with polished gold ornaments, wearing red coloured clothes, with beautiful black hair, wearing fresh flowers, being in the same young form as before, blameless Vaidehi was held in the arms of the fire god and presented to Rama.","words":[{"d":"विभावसुः","m":"fire god"},{"d":"तरुणादित्यसङ्काशम्","m":"radiating brightly like rising sun"},{"d":"तप्तकाञ्चनभूषणाम्","m":"adorned with polished gold ornaments"},{"d":"रक्ताम्बरधराम्","m":"wearing red coloured robes"},{"d":"नीलकुञ्चितमूर्थजाम्","m":"with beautiful black hair"},{"d":"अक्लिष्टमाल्याभरणाम्","m":"with fresh looking flowers"},{"d":"तथारूपाम्","m":"in the same form as before"},{"d":"अनिन्दिताम्","m":"blameless"},{"d":"बालाम्","m":"young"},{"d":"वैदेहीम्","m":"Vaidehi"},{"d":"अङ्के","m":"arms"},{"d":"कृत्वा","m":"holding"},{"d":"रामाय","m":"to Rama"},{"d":"ददौ","m":"gave"}]},{"v":4,"dev":"तरुणादित्यसङ्काशंतप्तकाञ्चनभूषणाम् ।रक्ताम्बरधरांबालांसीलकुञ्चितमूर्थजाम् अक्लिष्टमाल्याभरणांतथारूपामनिन्दिताम् ।ददौरामायवैदेहीमङ्केकृत्वाविभावसुः","trans":"Radiating like the rising sun, adorned with polished gold ornaments, wearing red coloured clothes, with beautiful black hair, wearing fresh flowers, being in the same young form as before, blameless Vaidehi was held in the arms of the fire god and presented to Rama.","words":[{"d":"विभावसुः","m":"fire god"},{"d":"तरुणादित्यसङ्काशम्","m":"radiating brightly like rising sun"},{"d":"तप्तकाञ्चनभूषणाम्","m":"adorned with polished gold ornaments"},{"d":"रक्ताम्बरधराम्","m":"wearing red coloured robes"},{"d":"नीलकुञ्चितमूर्थजाम्","m":"with beautiful black hair"},{"d":"अक्लिष्टमाल्याभरणाम्","m":"with fresh looking flowers"},{"d":"तथारूपाम्","m":"in the same form as before"},{"d":"अनिन्दिताम्","m":"blameless"},{"d":"बालाम्","m":"young"},{"d":"वैदेहीम्","m":"Vaidehi"},{"d":"अङ्के","m":"arms"},{"d":"कृत्वा","m":"holding"},{"d":"रामाय","m":"to Rama"},{"d":"ददौ","m":"gave"}]},{"v":5,"dev":"अब्रवीत्तुतदारामंसाक्षीलोकस्यपावकः ।एषातेराम वैदेहीपापमस्यां न विद्यते","trans":"Then the fire god who is a witness in the world, spoke to Rama,\" Here is your wife Vaidehi and she does not know any sin.\"","words":[{"d":"तदा","m":"then"},{"d":"लोकस्य","m":"in the world"},{"d":"साक्षी","m":"witness"},{"d":"पावकः","m":"fire god"},{"d":"रामम्","m":"to Rama"},{"d":"अब्रवीत्","m":"spoke तु you"},{"d":"राम","m":"Rama"},{"d":"एषा","m":"this way"},{"d":"ते","m":"you"},{"d":"वैदेही","m":"Vaidehi"},{"d":"अस्याम्","m":"she"},{"d":"पापम्","m":"sin"},{"d":"न विद्यते","m":"not know"}]},{"v":6,"dev":"नैववाचा न मनसानैवबुद्ध्या न चक्षुषा ।सुवृत्तावृत्तशौण्डीरन त्वामत्यचरच्छुभा","trans":"\"Sita is of good conduct and auspicious. To you who are endowed with valour, she is faithful by speech, by intention of thought and intellect and even by glance.\"","words":[{"d":"सुवृत्ता","m":"of good conduct"},{"d":"शुभा","m":"auspicious"},{"d":"वृत्तशौण्डीर","m":"endowed with valour"},{"d":"त्वाम्","m":"you"},{"d":"वाचा","m":"speech"},{"d":"न अत्यचरत्","m":"by intention"},{"d":"मनसा","m":"in the mind"},{"d":"न","m":"not"},{"d":"बुद्ध्या","m":"by intellect"},{"d":"नैव","m":"or else"},{"d":"चक्षुषा च","m":"even with eyes"}]},{"v":7,"dev":"रावणेनापनीतैषावीर्योसतिक्तेनरक्षसा ।त्वयाविरहितादीनाविवशानिर्जनाद्वनात्","trans":"\"When she was lonely, piteous, having no control, Rakshasa Ravana, who was proud of his valour abducted her from the forest when no one was there.\"","words":[{"d":"त्वया","m":"you"},{"d":"विरहिता","m":"lonely"},{"d":"दीना","m":"piteous"},{"d":"विवशा","m":"having no control"},{"d":"एषा","m":"she"},{"d":"वीर्योसतिक्तेन","m":"proud of valour"},{"d":"रक्षसा","m":"Rakshasa"},{"d":"रावणेन","m":"by Ravana"},{"d":"निर्जनात्","m":"when no one was there"},{"d":"वनात्","m":"from the forest"},{"d":"अपनीता","m":"abducted"}]},{"v":8,"dev":"रुद्धाचान्तःपुरेगुप्तात्वच्छित्तात्वत्परायणा ।रक्षिताराक्षसीभिश्चघोराभिर्घोरबुद्धिभिः","trans":"\"She was separated from you yet fully absorbed in you. She was kept in the gynaeceum secretly and guarded by frightful and ruthless Rakshasa women.\"","words":[{"d":"त्वच्छित्ता","m":"seperated from you"},{"d":"त्वत्परायणा","m":"fully absorbed in you"},{"d":"अन्तःपुरे","m":"in the gynaeceum"},{"d":"रुद्धा","m":"frightful"},{"d":"गुप्ता","m":"secretly"},{"d":"घोराभिः","m":"terrific"},{"d":"घोरबुद्धिभिः","m":"ruthless mind"},{"d":"राक्षसीभिः","m":"Rakshasa women"},{"d":"रक्षिता","m":"to guard"}]},{"v":9,"dev":"प्रलोभ्यमानाविविधंभर्त्स्यमाना च मैथिली ।नाचिन्तयततद्रक्षस्त्वद्गतेनान्तरात्मना","trans":"\" Although Mythili was tempted, threatened also, she had set her mind on you only and not thought of that Rakshasa.\"","words":[{"d":"विविधम्","m":"several"},{"d":"प्रलोभ्यमाना","m":"tempted"},{"d":"भर्त्स्यमाना","m":"threatened"},{"d":"मैथिली","m":"Mythili"},{"d":"त्वद्गतेन","m":"set her mind on you only"},{"d":"अन्तरात्मना","m":"in herself"},{"d":"तत्","m":"those"},{"d":"रक्षः","m":"Rakshasa"},{"d":"नाचिन्तयत","m":"not thought of"}]},{"v":10,"dev":"विशुद्धभावांनिष्पापांप्रतिगृह्णीष्वमैथिलीम् ।न किञ्चिरभिधातव्याअहमाज्ञापयामिते","trans":"\"Mythili is of untainted mind and a sinless one. Take her back without any reply, I am ordering you.\"","words":[{"d":"विशुद्धभावाम्","m":"untainted mind"},{"d":"निष्पापाम्","m":"sinless"},{"d":"मैथिलीम्","m":"Mythili"},{"d":"प्रतिगृह्णीष्व","m":"take her back"},{"d":"किञ्चित्","m":"indeed"},{"d":"न अभिदातव्या","m":"without any reply"},{"d":"अहम्","m":"I am"},{"d":"ते","m":"you"},{"d":"आज्ञापयामि","m":"order"}]},{"v":11,"dev":"ततःप्रीतिमानारामःश्रुत्यैवंवदतांवरः ।दध्यौमुहूर्तंधर्मात्माबाष्पव्याकुललोचनः","trans":"Then the supremely righteous Rama, who is good at speaking rejoiced at heart, his eyes filled with tears, thought for a moment.","words":[{"d":"ततः","m":"then"},{"d":"वदताम्","m":"good at speaking वरःsupreme"},{"d":"धर्मात्मा","m":"truthful"},{"d":"रामः","m":"Rama"},{"d":"एवम्","m":"all that"},{"d":"श्रुत्वा","m":"hearing"},{"d":"प्रीतमनाः","m":"rejoiced at heart"},{"d":"बाष्पव्याकुललोचनः","m":"eyes filled with tears"},{"d":"मुहूर्तम्","m":"for a moment"},{"d":"दध्यौ","m":"thought"}]},{"v":12,"dev":"एवमुक्तोमहातेजाधृतिमान्दृढविक्रमः ।उवाचत्रिदशश्रेष्ठंरामोधर्मभृतांवरः","trans":"Rama who is endowed with valour and firmness, and an upholder of dharma, a supreme person said to Brahma.","words":[{"d":"एवम्","m":"in that way"},{"d":"उक्तः","m":"spoken"},{"d":"धृतिमान्","m":"firm"},{"d":"दृढविक्रमः","m":"determined valour"},{"d":"धर्मभृताम्","m":"upholder of dharma"},{"d":"वरः","m":"supreme"},{"d":"रामः","m":"Rama"},{"d":"त्रिदशश्रेष्ठम्","m":"Brahma"},{"d":"उवाच","m":"said"}]},{"v":13,"dev":"अवश्यंत्रिषुलोकेषु न सीतापापमर्हति ।दीर्घकालोषिताहीयंरावणान्तःपुरेशुभा","trans":"\"That Sita is auspicious and has surely not done any sin is known to three worlds. But she lived long in the gynaeceum of Ravana.\"","words":[{"d":"सीता","m":"Sita"},{"d":"अवश्यम्","m":"surely"},{"d":"त्रिषुलोकेषु","m":"in the three worlds"},{"d":"पापम्","m":"sin"},{"d":"न अर्हति","m":"not done"},{"d":"शुभा","m":"auspicious"},{"d":"इयम्","m":"this"},{"d":"रावणान्तःपुरे","m":"in the gynaeceum of Ravana"},{"d":"दीर्घकालोषिताहि","m":"lived for log time"}]},{"v":14,"dev":"बालिशोखलुकामात्मारामोदशरथात्मजः ।इतिवक्ष्यन्तिमांसन्तोजानकीमविशोध्यहि","trans":"\"The people will surely say that mighty Dasharatha's son, Rama being lusty at heart has accepted Janaki without testing.\"","words":[{"d":"जानकीम्","m":"Janaki"},{"d":"अविशोद्य","m":"without testing"},{"d":"दशरथात्मजः","m":"Dasharatha's son"},{"d":"रामः","m":"Rama"},{"d":"बालिशः","m":"mighty"},{"d":"कामात्मा","m":"lusty at heart"},{"d":"खलु","m":"surely"},{"d":"इति","m":"thus"},{"d":"सन्त:","m":"people"},{"d":"माम्","m":"me"},{"d":"वक्ष्यन्ति","m":"will say"}]},{"v":15,"dev":"अनन्यहृदयांभक्तांमच्चित्तपरिवर्तिनीम् ।अहमप्यवगच्छामिमैथिलींजनकात्मजाम्","trans":"\"I also know that Mythili is ever coming around me with undivided love and is devoted to me.\"","words":[{"d":"मच्चित्तपरिवर्तिनीम्","m":"ever coming around me"},{"d":"जनकात्मजाम्","m":"Janaka's daughter"},{"d":"मैथिलीम्","m":"Mythili"},{"d":"अनन्यहृदयाम्","m":"undivided in her love"},{"d":"भक्ताम्","m":"devoted"},{"d":"अहमपि","m":"to me"},{"d":"अवगच्छामि","m":"I also know"}]},{"v":16,"dev":"इमामपिविशालाक्षींरक्षितांस्वेनतेजसा ।रावणोनातिवर्तेतवेलामिवमहोदधिः","trans":"\"Naturally she is selfeffulgent and can protect herself. Will Ravana be able to violate broad eyed Janakijust as the great ocean can't cross the bounds.\"","words":[{"d":"स्वेनतेजसा","m":"selfeffulgent"},{"d":"रक्षिताम्","m":"can protect herself"},{"d":"इमाम्","m":"her"},{"d":"विशालाक्षीम्","m":"broadeyed"},{"d":"महोदधिः","m":"great ocean"},{"d":"वेलामिव","m":"bounds"},{"d":"रावणः","m":"Ravana"},{"d":"नातिवर्तेत","m":"not violate"}]},{"v":17,"dev":"प्रत्ययार्थंतुलोकानांत्रयाणांसत्यसंश्रयः ।उपेक्षेचापिवैदेहींप्रविशन्तींहुताशनम्","trans":"\" As I am a follower of truth only, to convince the three worlds I was disregarding Vaidehi entering fire.\"","words":[{"d":"त्रयाणाम्","m":"three worlds"},{"d":"लोकानाम्","m":"in the world"},{"d":"प्रत्ययार्थम्","m":"to convince"},{"d":"हुताशनम्","m":"fire"},{"d":"प्रविशन्तीम्","m":"entering fire"},{"d":"वैदेहीम्","m":"Vaidehi"}]},{"v":18,"dev":"न हिशक्तःसुदुष्टात्मामनसापिहिमैथिलीम् ।प्रधर्षयितुमप्राप्यांदीप्तामग्निशिखामिव","trans":"\"It could not be possible for the evil minded Rakshasa to access or lay thoughts on Mythili who was glowing like flames of fire.\"","words":[{"d":"सुदुष्टात्मा","m":"evil minded"},{"d":"अप्राप्याम्","m":"inaccessible"},{"d":"मैथिलीम्","m":"Mythili"},{"d":"दीप्ताम्","m":"glowing"},{"d":"अग्निशिखामिव","m":"like flaming fire"},{"d":"मनसापि","m":"in thought also"},{"d":"प्रधर्षयितुम्","m":"exhibiting"},{"d":"न हिचशक्तः","m":"not possible"}]},{"v":19,"dev":"नेयमर्हतिचैश्वर्यंरावणान्तःपुरेशुभा ।अनन्याहिमयासीताभास्करेणप्रभायथा","trans":"\" Auspicious Sita would not have cared for the fortunes in the gynaeceum of Ravana. She is just like the radiance of the sun attached to the sun, attached to me and none other.\"","words":[{"d":"शुभा","m":"auspicious"},{"d":"इयम्","m":"she"},{"d":"रावणान्तःपुरे","m":"in the gynaeceum of Ravana"},{"d":"ऐश्वर्यम्","m":"fortune"},{"d":"सीता","m":"Sita"},{"d":"भास्करेण","m":"even sun"},{"d":"प्रभायथा","m":"like the radiance"},{"d":"मया","m":"by me"},{"d":"अनन्याहि","m":"other than"}]},{"v":20,"dev":"विशुद्धात्रिषुलोकेषुमैथिलीजनकात्मजा ।न विहातुंमयाशक्याकीर्तिरात्ववतायथा","trans":"\"Mythili is unsullied in the three worlds. Renouncing her is not feasible just as fame and as she is like my own self.\"","words":[{"d":"जनकात्मजा","m":"Janaka's daughter"},{"d":"मैथिली","m":"Mythili"},{"d":"त्रिषुलोकेषु","m":"in the three worlds"},{"d":"विशुध्धा","m":"unsullied"},{"d":"आत्मवता","m":"from self"},{"d":"कीर्तिःयथा","m":"like fame"},{"d":"मया","m":"by me"},{"d":"विहातुम्","m":"to renounce"},{"d":"न शक्या","m":"not feasible"}]},{"v":21,"dev":"अवश्यं च मयाकार्यंसर्वेषांवोवचोहितम् ।स्निग्धानांलोकनाधानामेवं च वदतांहितम्","trans":"\"You are worship worthy of the world and loving people advising me in this way. Your words of good advice are good to all and for me. I will certainly follow.\"","words":[{"d":"स्निग्धानाम्","m":"loving"},{"d":"लोकनाथानाम्","m":"worship worthy of the world"},{"d":"एवम्","m":"in this way"},{"d":"हितम्","m":"good advice"},{"d":"वदताम्","m":"speaking"},{"d":"वःसर्वेषाम्","m":"to all"},{"d":"हितम्","m":"good"},{"d":"मया","m":"by me"},{"d":"अवश्यम्","m":"certainly"},{"d":"कार्यम्","m":"will do"}]}]}